items.fromString:
SO THAT ... 
We can demonstrate outside of Jenkins that a logged in user can, from the browser, invoke both platform and business REST web services.

WE NEED ...
Platfomr Futures IB-Auth spike to be deployable in an environment allowing:
User logon to IB-Auth
Selection of CWA/M OR alternative session based browser client 
Invocation of a Platofmr Service (e.g. /switches')
Invocation of Business service (e.g. .../arrangements) 
Ability to display requet and associated web service response

NOTE:
Ideally this SHOULD be demonstrable on/in WAS.  Locally demonstrable COULD suffice in timescale

ISSUE: There is anecdotal evidence that WAS deployment may have configuration issues compared to non-WAS built/tested artifacts

items.fromString:
SO THAT …	
A platform service enabling the ability to provide non-server-side user journey clients of IB-Auth to read the pre-fetched 'snapshot' of a retail customer identified by the individuals party-id identifier accessing information held in the HTTPSession via the IB Auth SDS interface

WE NEED …	
To build and java based test REST-capable ‘snapshot' service:
1.	Design ‘out-to-in’ snapshot resource API (Swagger)
2.	Generate client and server to use as java interface definition
3.	Use server interface definition to implement resource server
4.	Implement any data transform
5.	Create Wrapper interface over IB-Auth SDS interface to query the snapshot

SUCCESS IS …	
1.	Demonstrate ability to fetch the party snapshot conformant to Swagger defined API 
2.	Demonstrate no impact on IB-Auth core codebase
items.toString:
SO THAT …	
A platform service enabling the ability to provide non-server-side user journey clients of IB-Auth to read the pre-fetched 'snapshot' of a retail customer identified by the individuals party-id identifier accessing information held in the HTTPSession via the IB Auth SDS interface.  

The service must allow the client to request a 'snippet' (manifest as a 'child resource') of the snapshot (embedded hypermedia links within the snapshot representation) and 'null' a value of the snapshot if updated by the client within the user journey via invocation of a separate service call

WE NEED …	
To build and java based test REST-capable ‘snapshot' service:
1.	Design ‘out-to-in’ snapshot resource API (Swagger)
2.	Generate client and server to use as java interface definition
3.	Use server interface definition to implement resource server
4.	Implement any data transform
5.	Create Wrapper interface over IB-Auth SDS interface to query the snapshot

SUCCESS IS …	
1.	Demonstrate ability to fetch the party snapshot conformant to Swagger defined API 
2.	Demonstrate no impact on IB-Auth core codebase
